    Constructor
  </Paragraph>
  <Section Title="Description">
    <Paragraph>
      The <TypeRef>WindowInfoXlib</TypeRef> constructor creates a platform binding structure and initializes the inherited <TypeRef>structureSizeInBytes</TypeRef> and type discriminator fields.
    </Paragraph>
  </Section>
  <Section Title="Usage">
    <Code Language="C++"><![CDATA[WindowInfoXlib(::Display* display, ::Window window, const V2UInt32& windowSizeInPixels);]]></Code>
    <SubSection Title="Argument list">
      <ArgumentList>
        <ArgumentListEntry Type="::Display*" Name="display">
          The Xlib display connection.
        </ArgumentListEntry>
        <ArgumentListEntry Type="::Window" Name="window">
          The Xlib window to bind.
        </ArgumentListEntry>
        <ArgumentListEntry Type="const V2UInt32&amp;" Name="windowSizeInPixels">
          The current drawable window size in pixels.
        </ArgumentListEntry>
      </ArgumentList>
    </SubSection>
  </Section>
